        "Node name for S&R": "MarkdownNote"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "# BrainDead — TRELLIS.2 Shape → Textured Mesh\n\nSingle-image to **PBR-textured 3D mesh** with Microsoft TRELLIS.2. Drop in a reference image, get back a watertight mesh with base-color / metallic / roughness vertex attributes.\n\n## Flow\n1. **Load Image** — pick any reference image (front-facing subject works best).\n2. **Trellis2 Remove Background** — produces a clean foreground mask.\n3. **BD TRELLIS.2 Get Conditioning** — DinoV3 conditioning (carries resolution / VRAM config).\n4. **BD TRELLIS.2 Image to Shape** — sparse-structure + shape sampling → untextured geometry.\n5. **BD TRELLIS.2 Shape to Textured Mesh** — PBR texture sampling → textured `trimesh` + voxelgrid.\n6. **BD Preview 3D** — interactive viewer for the textured mesh.\n\n## Models / VRAM\n`microsoft/TRELLIS.2-4B` auto-downloads on first run (resolved via `extra_model_paths.yaml`); no loader-node `models` block needed. Defaults use the `1024_cascade` resolution and `max_tokens=49152` (~9 GB just for the cascade). Budget **~20 GB VRAM** end to end; the RTX PRO 6000 (97 GB) runs it comfortably in `keep_loaded` mode. Lower `max_tokens` or use the `512` resolution to cut VRAM. Requires the `flash_attn` backend + CuMesh.\n\n## Tips\n- Raise `ss_sampling_steps` / `shape_sampling_steps` for more shape detail (slower).\n- Reuse one `shape_result` and feed a different `texture_conditioning` to retexture without regenerating geometry (or use **BD TRELLIS.2 Retexture**).\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ],
      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead TRELLIS.2"
    },
